				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$B\left(2\theta \right)=\frac{K\lambda }{L{\mathrm{cos}}\theta }$$\end{document}
where θ is Bragg’s angle, λ is the wavelength of X-rays, and K is the constant equal to 0.94 for cubic and 0.89 for spherical crystallites. In this work, K = 0.90.

